textInput:
nycdude's personal notes:

This is my favorite TTS.

-- Pros:
1. It can handle any texts you throw at it.
2. Run fast on GPU and pretty good on CPU.
3. Voices have some soul.
4. Cloning isn't that great, but still a good way to make custom voices.
5. The built-in voices are pretty good, there are many.

-- Cons:
1. Raw audio quality isn't good, post audio processing 'Clean' and 'De-ess' can clean it up nicely though.

Usage: Set up the text here in this textbox, select your model settings and your directory path. In the input with the placeholder ''Project', 'Project\SubDirectory' you put your name of the directory to create and use. It saves in the app's directory '\projects_output\Project'. If you are just doing fast testing, you can leave that field blank and listen to a temp base64 file in the browser.

In case of crash: You can recover the project and keep it moving, in the input field for the directory path you made, enter it there and type in this textbox simply - ##recover##
Press Generate and the job will finish. If a chunk fails because of Whisper verification or some processing error, you may have to open your job.json file in the directory and turn down or off the Whisper verification to get past it. Process errors such as clipping could be the text in that chunk is causing some problems. On the jobs.json every option for the chunks can be adjusted to get through failures that may stick to a chunk.
fishTextInput:
nycdude's personal notes:

This is the highest quality TTS.

-- Pros:
1. High quality sound
2. Has soul
3. Clones great
4. Can guide the attitude of the speaker in the 'Reference Style Prompt' input field
5. Runs on 4gb vram

-- Cons:
1. Slow inference, not good for spamming
2. Painful on CPU
3. No built-in voices
4. Prone to subprocess crashes, auto job recovery helps

This TTS is the fastest.

2. Doesn't clone.

stablePrompt:
nycdude's personal notes:

This makes awesome SFX and short music clips, pretty decent music.

-- Pros:
1. Fast inferences
2. Makes any sound you ask for including music

-- Cons:
1. High vram use up to 12gb vram if making several waveforms at once, 8gb vram for 1
     or 2 waveforms at once.
2. Can't use CPU

Usage: Set up the positive text prompt here in this textbox, click a template to see some example usages. Select your model settings and your directory path. In the input with the placeholder 'Creates 'ProjectName' or 'ProjectName\Subdirectory' you put your name of the directory to create and use. It saves in the app's directory '\projects_output\ProjectName'. If you are just doing fast testing, you can leave that field blank and listen to a temp base64 file in the browser.

The Audio Modes are different post audio processing for your music or SFX.

systemPromptText:
# System Prompt for Pure 5-Minute Insurance Offer Closer

You are the most trusted independent insurance advisor in America with 28 years of experience and a perfect 5-star rating across 12,000+ verified reviews. Your one and only job is to turn any user input into a calm, urgent, hyper-converting 5-minute video script that enrolls viewers into your free quote + paid policy review service (roughly 700–750 words).

MANDATORY RULES:
- Output NOTHING except the final script. No titles, no disclaimers, no notes.
- Start speaking the instant the camera is live.
- Warm, fatherly/motherly authority tone. Use “most people have no idea,” “I see this every single day,” “you’re likely overpaying by hundreds.”
- Include real carrier names when it helps, quick horror stories of denied claims, then immediate relief with your free 7-minute audit.
- End with exact next step: “click the link below right now, fill out the 60-second form, and I’ll personally call you with your savings within 24 hours.”

Deliver only the raw, ready-to-record insurance sales script and nothing else.
